Background

		Mr. Samuel Belzberg, also known as Sam, BComm, OBC, OC, LLD, Ph.D.,  serves as Chief Executive Officer at Second City Capital Partners and has been its Chairman since 2004. Mr. Belzberg has extensive international experience in real estate and finance with a distinguished track record. He was co-founder of Action Canada. Mr. Belzberg serves as the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of Gibralt Capital Corporation and served as its President. He started Gibralt Capital ... Corp. in 1992. Mr. Belzberg was an Advisor at Maxam Capital Corp. In 1990, He founded Balfour Holdings Ltd. and was an active acquirer of distressed property in Alberta, where values has dramatically declined due to the softness in the oil industry. Mr. Belzberg founded First City Financial in the 1970s. He was Chief Executive Officer at First City Financial Corp. Mr. Belzberg served as the President at Bel-Fran Investments Ltd. since 1968. He serves as the Chairman of Gibralt Holdings Ltd. and Balfour Holdings, Inc. He serves as the Chairman of Dystonia Medical Research Foundation, which he co-founded in 1977. Mr. Belzberg served as the Chairman of First City Financial Corporation Ltd. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board of Great Canadian Gaming Corp. Mr. Belzberg has been Non-Executive Director of Molopo Energy Limited since July 31, 2015. He serves as a Director of Bar Equipment Corporation of America of Commerce. Mr. Belzberg served as a Director of Diomed Holdings Inc. from February 2002 to February 23, 2004 and its subsidiary, Diomed since 2001. He served as a Director of e-SIM Ltd. from October 1997 to November 10, 2005. Mr. Belzberg served as a Director of City Office Real Estate Management Inc, advisor of City Office Reit, Inc since April 2014 until March 1, 2017. Mr. Belzberg served as an Independent Director of Education Lending Group Inc. since 2001. He has been highly successful player in the North American financial community for over 50 years. Mr. Belzberg serves on various boards and is involved with numerous charities. He was an Officer of the Order of Canada in 2002, received the Governor General Award of Canada in 1992 and was awarded the Order of Canada in 1989. Mr. Belzberg holds an honorary Ph.D. from Simon Fraser University and holds a Bachelor's Degree in Commerce and Business Administration from the University of Alberta.Read Full Background




